{
  "name": "courtly",
  "description": "A concert harp cascading through a sunlit hall while pizzicato strings dance underneath. Plucked strings both soft (harp, round and shimmering) and short (pizzicato, dry and bouncy) — a low harp string grounds the cascade, a mid harp pluck rolls through the melody like a glissando fragment, a pizzicato violin and soft cello pizzicato dance a bouncing counter-line, high harp harmonics ring flute-pure, tiny top-octave flicks tumble into delay echoes, a bowed arco swell blooms warm underneath, and rolled harp chords shimmer up like a harpist's sweeping hand. Elegant, cascading, regal but playful and bright — all sparkle and grace. A major @ A=432, additive and clean, lush hall reverb with taste. Every register covered, never dreary, never harsh.",
